{
  "text": "Paraproteins are well recognized as a source of interference in laboratory assays [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] and the diseases associated with them can be associated with specific clinical complications. We report a patient with myeloma and an IgA paraprotein, with acquired von Willebrand disease, in whom biochemistry analysis was complicated by formation of a gel within the separated serum. We postulate that both these conditions were contributory to the analytical problem.",
